    <section id="ben-ming-nian">
      <h2>What Is Ben Ming Nian?</h2>
      <p><strong>Ben Ming Nian</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">本命年</span>, "origin life year") is the year that shares your birth animal. In traditional Chinese belief, this year brings <strong>Fan Tai Sui</strong> (犯太歲) — a spiritual confrontation with the Grand Duke Jupiter, the celestial authority presiding over the year. This confrontation creates instability but also opportunities for profound personal development.</p>
      <p>Traditional protective measures include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Wearing red</strong> — red underwear, socks, or a waistband throughout the year, ideally gifted by a family member</li>
        <li><strong>Tai Sui prayers</strong> — visiting a temple early in the year to pay respects to the year's Tai Sui general</li>
        <li><strong>Jade or obsidian amulets</strong> — protective stones worn close to the body</li>
        <li><strong>Humility and caution</strong> — avoiding boastfulness and unnecessary risk</li>
        <li><strong>Charitable acts</strong> — donating blood, volunteering, or giving to charity to accumulate positive karma</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="career">
      <h2>Career &amp; Finance</h2>
      <p>Ben Ming Nian brings <strong>career turbulence</strong>. Job changes, restructurings, and shifts in professional direction are common. The Horse's ambitious nature is amplified but met with resistance from Tai Sui energy. The key is to <strong>prepare for change rather than resist it</strong> — have backup plans, maintain professional relationships, and keep skills current.</p>
      <p><strong>Finance</strong> requires particular caution. The doubled Fire energy creates impulsive spending and speculative temptations. Conservative financial management is essential — build emergency reserves in the first quarter and avoid major purchases or investments during volatile months (June, October). Do not lend money or make financial guarantees for others.</p>
      <p><strong>Entrepreneurial ventures</strong> started in Ben Ming Nian carry higher risk. If possible, delay launches to the following year. If commitment is unavoidable, proceed with thorough preparation and multiple contingency plans.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="love">
      <h2>Love &amp; Relationships</h2>
      <p>Romantic relationships face the <strong>most intense pressure</strong> of Ben Ming Nian. Existing partnerships are tested as both partners confront fundamental questions about compatibility, direction, and commitment. Relationships with strong foundations deepen through honest confrontation; fragile relationships may not survive the year's scrutiny.</p>
      <p><strong>Single Horses</strong> may experience intense but unstable romantic connections. The doubled Fire energy creates powerful attraction but little stability. Relationships that begin in 2026 should be allowed to develop slowly — rushing into commitment during a Ben Ming Nian often leads to later regret.</p>
      <p><strong>Family relationships</strong> require patience. The Horse's amplified independence may clash with family expectations. Communication and compromise are essential.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="health">
      <h2>Health &amp; Wellness</h2>
      <p>Health is the area where Ben Ming Nian demands the <strong>greatest attention</strong>. Doubled Fire energy creates risk of cardiovascular strain, inflammation, eye problems, and mental health challenges (anxiety, insomnia, mood swings). Annual health check-ups at the year's start are strongly recommended.</p>
      <p><strong>Heart health</strong> is the top priority. Monitor blood pressure, manage stress actively, and maintain cardiovascular fitness through regular moderate exercise. Avoid extreme sports or unnecessarily dangerous activities during the year.</p>
      <p><strong>Mental health</strong> deserves equal focus. The intensity of Ben Ming Nian can trigger existential questioning and emotional turbulence. Meditation, counselling, time in nature, and creative expression all serve as healthy outlets. Water-element activities (swimming, visiting the ocean) help cool excess Fire.</p>
      <p><strong>Travel safety</strong> requires extra caution. Drive carefully, follow safety protocols, and avoid unnecessary risk-taking. Ben Ming Nian is statistically associated with minor accidents and injuries — awareness and prevention are the best strategies.</p>
    </section>

